/*When a square is circumscribed (square inside the circle) by a circle , the diagonal of the square is equal to the diameter of the circle.*/

/*When a circle is inscribed (square outside the circle) in a square , the diameter of the circle is equal to the side length of the square.*/

/*Area=1/2*diagnal^2
*/

def square_areas_difference(r):
	area_inner = 0.5 * ((r*2)**2)
	area_outside = (r*2)**2
	return area_outside - area_inner
